<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">
<html tal:omit-tag="" 
  i18n:domain="silva_news"
  tal:define="vein string:edit;">

<metal:use-macro use-macro="context/macro_asset_edit/macros/editor">

<metal:block fill-slot="title_metadata">
<tr class="top-controls">
  <td colspan="3">
  <h3>Select checkboxes to limit the Subjects and Target Audiences that will appear in your News Filters and News Articles</h3>
 </td>
</tr>
</metal:block>
    
<metal:block fill-slot="title_editor">
<tbody>
  <tr>
    <th class="align-right" width="12%" i18n:translate="">element</th>
    <th i18n:translate="">content</th>
    <th i18n:translate="">description</th>
  </tr>
  <tal:repeat repeat="field form/get_fields">
  <tr tal:attributes="class python:repeat['field'].odd() and 'odd' or 'even'">
    <td class="field-title">
      <label tal:attributes="for field/id" tal:content="python:field['title']" style="text-transform:capitalize;" />
      <span class="warning" tal:condition="python:field.is_required()">*</span>
    </td>
    <td>
      <div style="float: left;">
        <input tal:replace="structure python:field.render_from_request(request)" />
      </div>
    </td>
    <td  tal:content="structure python:field.get_value('description')" >
      description
    </td>
  </tr>
  </tal:repeat>
</tbody>
<tfoot>
  <tr class="controls">
    <td class="align-right" colspan="3">
      <input type="hidden" name="cur_set" value="text" />
      <input class="button"
        type="submit"
        name="submit:method"
        value="save selection"
        title="access key: alt-s"
        accesskey="s"
        i18n:attributes="title;value"
      />
    </td>
  </tr>
</tfoot>
</metal:block>

<metal:fill-slot fill-slot="info">
  <div class="info">
    <h3 i18n:translate="">
      <img tal:replace="structure icon" /><abbr title="Silva News Network">SNN</abbr> Category Filters
    </h3>
    <p>These filters allow users to limit the lists of subjects and target audiences available to filters and news and agenda items. When a Category Filter is created in a branch of a site, all underlying items will be affected.</p>
    <p>You may select any number of subjects or target audiences, and only those selected will appear in the edit screns.  If, however, you don't select any items in a category, <u>all</u> items in that category will appear.</p>
  </div>
</metal:fill-slot>

</metal:use-macro>

</html>